This paper deals with secure communication over a wireless network, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of relays and multiple-access channels suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The proposed scheme involves beamforming and interference alignment, which are techniques commonly used in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of artificial noise, which is a technique used in multimedia systems (cs.MM) to improve the quality of transmitted signals.
